org.docgene.help.gui.swing.autocomplete

Class JAutoComplete

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.docgene.help.gui.swing.autocomplete.JAutoComplete
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoComplete

    public class JAutoComplete
extends java.lang.Object
implements AutoComplete
    An Autocomplete class, usable with a JTextComponent, which allows to add Autocomplete behavior to the text component. This class allows to show a Popup window with the list of possible choices and allow to choose between these choices.

    Customization

    The class can also be customized through several properties:
    • setOpacity(float): the opacity of the Popup Window
    • acceptDuplicates(boolean): true if the dictionnary accept duplicates
    Moreover, it is possible to customize the way the list of suggestions is presented, and to change the default search engine used to check for hits.

    Example

     JTextField tf = new JTextField(10);
 AutoComplete2 autoCompleter = new AutoComplete2(tf);
 autoCompleter.setOpacity(0.9f);

 //add the dictionary
 autoCompleter.addToDictionary("hello");
 autoCompleter.addToDictionary("highlight");
 autoCompleter.addToDictionary("cruel world");
 autoCompleter.addToDictionary("war");
 autoCompleter.addToDictionary("wording");
 autoCompleter.addToDictionary("world");
